{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"struct","roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO19IOExtensionPointRefV","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"IOExtensionPointRef","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"IOExtensionPointRef","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"IOExtensionPointRef"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/init(_:)-1jnvs","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/init(_:)-1r9zs","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/init(_:)-58vbs","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/init(_:)-5gpby","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/init(_:)-6nw6k","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"]},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/ptr"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"title":"Type Methods","anchor":"Type-Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/lookup(name:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/register(name:)"]},{"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/IOExtensionPointProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOExtensionPoint"},{"text":" provides a mechanism for modules to extend the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functionality of the library or application that loaded it in an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"organized fashion."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointProtocol"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"IOExtensionPointRef","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An extension point is identified by a name, and it may optionally"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"require that any implementation must be of a certain type (or derived","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"thereof). Use [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.IOExtensionPoint.register"},{"type":"text","text":"] to register an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"extension point, and [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.IOExtensionPoint.set_required_type"},{"type":"text","text":"] to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set a required type.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A module can implement an extension point by specifying the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[type[Type_](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/type_] that implements the functionality. Additionally, each","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"implementation of an extension point has a name, and a priority. Use","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.IOExtensionPoint.implement"},{"type":"text","text":"] to implement an extension point."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"c","type":"codeListing","code":["GIOExtensionPoint *ep;","","\/\/ Register an extension point","ep = g_io_extension_point_register (\"my-extension-point\");","g_io_extension_point_set_required_type (ep, MY_TYPE_EXAMPLE);"]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["\/\/ Implement an extension point","G_DEFINE_TYPE (MyExampleImpl, my_example_impl, MY_TYPE_EXAMPLE)","g_io_extension_point_implement (\"my-extension-point\",","                                my_example_impl_get_type (),","                                \"my-example\",","                                10);"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is up to the code that registered the extension point how","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it uses the implementations that have been associated with it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Depending on the use case, it may use all implementations, or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"only the one with the highest priority, or pick a specific"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"one by name.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To avoid opening all modules just to find out what extension"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"points they implement, GIO makes use of a caching mechanism,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"gio-querymodules.html","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You are expected to run this command after installing a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GIO module."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GIO_EXTRA_MODULES","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable can be used to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"specify additional directories to automatically load modules","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from. This environment variable has the same syntax as the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"PATH","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". If two modules have the same base name in different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directories, then the latter one will be ignored. If additional"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"directories are specified GIO will load modules from the built-in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"directory last.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"code":"GIOExtensionPoint","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOExtensionPoint"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPoint","type":"reference"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef"},{"text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOExtensionPoint"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/ioextensionpointref"]}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/IOExtensionPointRef/IOExtensionPointProtocol-Implementations":{"role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/ioextensionpointref\/ioextensionpointprotocol-implementations","abstract":[],"title":"IOExtensionPointProtocol Implementations","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointRef\/IOExtensionPointProtocol-Implementations","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/IOExtensionPointProtocol":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOExtensionPointProtocol"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/ioextensionpointprotocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOExtensionPointProtocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOExtensionPointProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOExtensionPoint"},{"text":" provides a mechanism for modules to extend the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functionality of the library or application that loaded it in an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"organized fashion."}],"title":"IOExtensionPointProtocol","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/IOExtensionPointRef/init(gconstpointer:)":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Conditional initialiser from an optional, non-mutable "},{"code":"gconstpointer","type":"codeVoice"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\